headline.print_headline: Calorie Counts on Menus Used by Women, Wealthier Diners in Seattle Area
headline.main: Calorie Counts on Menus Used by Women, Wealthier Diners in Seattle Area

docs.lead_paragraph: Women, higher-income diners and patrons of fast-food restaurants in the Seattle area are more likely to use restaurant calorie count information, according to survey results published on Tuesday.
docs.snippet: Women, higher-income diners and patrons of fast-food restaurants in the Seattle area are more likely to use restaurant calorie count information, according to survey results published on Tuesday.

docs.abstract: Cristian Tomasetti and Bert Vogelstein study in journal Science concluding that many cancers are caused by random genetic mutations and are in essence unpreventable has triggered backlash and despair among some; accepting role of random chance in biology and humans' limited ability to control phenomena, however, can also be liberating.
docs.lead_paragraph: Though we long for control, chance plays a powerful role in the biology of cancer and the evolution of life.
docs.snippet: Though we long for control, chance plays a powerful role in the biology of cancer and the evolution of life.
